<subSubSection lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1723,1964]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1904,1928]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name derives from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[732,821,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">falcatus</emphasis>
= sickle-shaped”; referring to the epiphallus which, in lateral view, is decidedly reminiscent of a sickle blade.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,1967,2021]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
